<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62c5f93c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3744"><num value="3744">§ 3744.</num><heading> Federal, State and local authority</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62c5f93d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3744/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Disclaimer</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to supersede or limit the authority of Federal, State or local agencies otherwise authorized by law to provide services to Indians.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62c5f93e-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3744/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Duplication of services</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall work with all appropriate Federal departments and agencies to avoid duplication of programs and services currently available to Indian tribes and landowners from other sources.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id62c5f93f-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/177/tIII/s304">Pub. L. 103–177, title III, § 304</ref>, <date date="1993-12-03">Dec. 3, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/2022">107 Stat. 2022</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
